    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>This blogpost is not finished yet :)</strong></p>

<p>This is basically an implementation of <a href="http://freespace.virgin.net/hugo.elias/models/m_perlin.htm">this great article</a> on Perlin Noise in JavaScript, mainly so that I gain a little understanding on how it works.</p>

<h3>The Noise Function</h3>

<p>A noise function is the foundation of the perlin noise that we want to generate. You are probably familiar the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematics">mathematical definition</a>) of a function, i.e. <em>[&#8230;] a relation between a set of inputs and a set of permissible outputs [&#8230;]</em>.</p>

<div markdown="0">
\[
    f(Seed, Time) \rightarrow Noise
 \]
</div>




